article.headline: Liberty 68, Coastal Carolina 55
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Seth Curry and Brolin Floyd scored 15 points each to lead Liberty to a 68-55 victory over Coastal Carolina on Monday night. Curry, the nation's top freshman scorer at 20.4 points a game entering Monday, missed all six of his 3-point attempts, but Floyd was 6 of 9 from the field for Liberty (12-6, 3-3 Big South Conference). Coastal Carolina (7-10, 1-4), which has lost three consecutive games, led by as many as eight points midway through the first half, but the Flames rallied for a 35-29 halftime lead. The Chanticleers tied the score at 37 on Anthony Breeze's two free throws with 16:31 left in the game, but Liberty took charge from that point, leading by 15 with 1:05 remaining. Anthony Smith added 14 points for Liberty and Logan Johnson had eight assists. Joseph Harris led Coastal Carolina with 19 points and 11 rebounds.
